title: Table cover

Medium: linen
Technique: plain weave cloth with bobbin lace insertions
description: Linen table cover with hemstitching and six pieces of lace insertion showing Indian motifs: two rectangular pieces show two braves with bows framing tepees and four squares in the corners show a man in a canoe, a woman with a papoose, a brave with a bow, and a tepee.
